message: Removed Malay Language, as it is not an Indian /South Asian language, but an Austronesian South East Asian language.  Malay may be spoken as a second language, but is not the original ethnic language of any person of South Asian descent in Malaysia.

Include information about Moors who have Sinhalese ancestry, as the article completely omitted that aspect out. There are two classes of Muslim Moors in Sri Lanka, those with Sinhalese Buddhist Maternal lineage, and those with Tamil Maternal lineage, while both share paternal lineage from Arab traders.

Undid revision 846856010 by [[Special:Contributions/Hzh|Hzh]] ([[User talk:Hzh|talk]]) His silence about the religious riots between Hindus and Sikhs in which thousands of Sikhs died is a factual controversy that was raised by Sikh communities in Malaysia in the past. So an important point in his life, that is not a POV but a fact.
Fact - Tamil majority regions of Northern Sri Lanka are being presently administered by the Sri Lankan government. Government and geopgrahic island are two different things.
Put ethnicity to his language/ethnic group. Indian is not an ethnicity, but a nationality/subcontinental social construct.

Undid revision 841149691 by [[Special:Contributions/118.200.6.228|118.200.6.228]] ([[User talk:118.200.6.228|talk]]) He opposes death penalty, yet he was silent on the genocide of Sikhs by the Indian government. He should have opposed genocide and killings in general, especially pertaining to the Sikh community of which he is part of. The Sikh genocide is an integral history of the Sikh community globally

Nick Krygios is of Greek parentage, and he considers himself so. There is no where in his autobiography of him claiming to be ethnic Tamil by culture or identity. His father is of greek Australian descent, while his mother comes from a royal family, which would predominantely indicate Malay ancestry. Even if there may be Tamil ancestry from his mother's side (supposition), that is not the culture they follow nor the language they speak. Please consult with him, prior to posting his information.

Indian is not an ethnicity, therefore, not an ethnic group. There are many ethnic group within Indians, ethnicity and language are tied with each others. Tamils form an ethnic group, Punjabis an ethnic group, Sindhis an ethnic group, Malayalees an ethnic group.  Indian is a collective subcontinental terminology, a social construct to denote their origins from the Indian subcontinent which is home to many ethnic groups.
